Review: One of the greatest films of all time. God I love this shit. I fucking LOVE AI and consciousness shit! And the whole “is it killing if I’m not technically alive?” thing? Fuck yeah! Gets me so hyped lemme fuckin tell you god damn. And Oscar Isaac being a sneaky drunk genius I can’t get ENOUGH of it.

In a world of remakes and IP guzzling, this movie was a breath of fresh air. A fantastic and exciting story that is as exciting and action packed as it is sentimental and emotional. Viola Davis brings her usual god tier performance to a role we’ve always wanted from one of the most intimidating actresses of our time. Lashana Lynch plays the most precise and fun (and hot) character I’ve seen in a movie in the last few years.
Porn horror from A24, how could I possibly say no?
Having seen this as a kid, I cannot tell you enough how gripping the anticipation for the brothel scene was upon rewatch.
Church scene is fire, bout it tho…
Barry Keoghan’s acting and back muscles really slingshotted this thing into the whatthefuck-verse, god what a raucous and sexy time.

Movie: Master and Commander: The Far Side of the World
Review: A pretty perfect “holiday gone wrong” rom-com flick.

If I had a nickel for every movie I’ve ever watched that’s perfect, nearly all of those nickels would be from Denis. This movie is worth every millisecond of screen time. The whole movie is great but I can’t help but marvel at how the first thing K does with his newfound “humanity”…is lie. Fuckin stellar.
God I want to try that spaghetti…
Karl Urban’s scowl and Lena Headey’s smirk have never looked better.
